# Project Architecture

**Help & Grow** is an **AI Native Expert Network**: everyone can be **both expert and learner**; we pair people for paid sessions, AI matching, and mem9-backed context, moving toward *service as agent* (always-on digital experts that learn from the human expert). See `docs/BRAND.md`.

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|-------|-----------|
| Framework | Next.js 15 (App Router) |
| Language | TypeScript (strict) |
| Database | PostgreSQL (e.g. Supabase) via Prisma 7 |
| ORM | Prisma with `@prisma/adapter-pg` |
| Auth | NextAuth.js (Google OAuth + Email magic links) |
| UI | Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui components |
| AI | Alibaba DashScope (Qwen) — LLM, image, TTS, ASR |
| Memory | mem9 — persistent cloud memory per expert agent |
| Hosting | Vercel (serverless) |

## Deployments

| Deployment | URL | AI Provider | Database |
|-----------|-----|-------------|----------|
| Origin (production) | expert-network.vercel.app | Qwen (DashScope) | PostgreSQL |
| Hackathon | expert-network-hackathon.vercel.app | Gemini (Vertex AI) | Supabase PostgreSQL |

This codebase targets the **origin** deployment. Changes go to `main` branch → auto-deploy via Vercel.

## Database

- Provider: `postgresql` in `prisma/schema.prisma` (enforced by `scripts/switch-db.mjs`)
- No `url` in datasource block (Prisma 7 reads `DATABASE_URL` automatically)
- `DATABASE_URL` must be `postgresql://`; MySQL URLs are rejected in `src/lib/prisma.ts`
- Arrays: prefer one-to-many relations or JSON as needed for Postgres

## Key Directories

```
src/app/api/          → API routes (Next.js Route Handlers)
src/app/              → Pages (App Router)
src/lib/ai/           → AI provider implementations (Qwen, Gemini)
src/lib/integrations/ → External service integrations (TTS, memory, etc.)
src/components/       → Shared React components
src/hooks/            → Custom React hooks
prisma/               → Database schema
scripts/              → Build-time scripts (e.g. switch-db)
hiclaw/service/       → HiClaw shadow service (Express): manager, shadow/evaluator/planner workers, store (Postgres HTTP SQL or pg)
```

## HiClaw shadow service

Separate Node process documented in `hiclaw/README.md`. Session store: Postgres via HTTP SQL or `pg` (`DB9_*` / `HICLAW_POSTGRES_URL`). Next.js uses the same HiClaw tables via `src/lib/tidb.ts` (Postgres). Design: `docs/design-docs/hiclaw-agent-harness-db9.md`.

